node_id,00-00-00.00-00-00.00-00-00,,
node_nam,FROID namespace,,
node_tag,FROID_NS,,
flio_own,00-00-00.00-00-00.00-00-00,,
flio_crt,00-00-00.01-02-00.00-00-01.00-00-00,,
NODE_TAG,NODE_ID,NODE_NAM,Definition
FROID_NS,00-00-00.00-00-00.00-00-00,FROID namespace,The logical space composed of all valid identifier positions.
FROID,01-00-00.00-00-00.00-00-00,"FROID, Inc.","The company-level identity at OID position 1 (VV=01); the entity that owns and develops the framework."
NODE_ID,00-00-00.00-01-00.00-00-00,Node Location Identifier,A unique 9-segment identifier that denotes a position in the namespace and identifies a node when assigned.
NODE_NAM,00-00-00.00-01-00.01-00-00,Human readable name,A descriptive label assigned to a node for human interpretation.
NODE_TAG,00-00-00.00-01-00.02-00-00,Human parseable short name,A concise identifier used for human-readable tagging of a node.
NOD_DEF,00-00-00.00-01-00.03-00-00,One-sentence description of a node,The single declarative sentence describing the node identified by a NODE_ID; carried in the Definition column of the index.
FOLIO,00-00-00.00-03-00.00-00-00,FROID namespace realization of a node,A concrete grouping of a node's manifest and associated artifacts.
FLIO_REF,00-00-00.00-03-00.01-00-00,Manifest file of folio contents,A manifest that enumerates all artifacts belonging to a node.
FLIO_ART,00-00-00.00-03-00.02-00-00,Any member of a folio,A payload item associated with a node and referenced by its manifest.
FLIO_ATH,00-00-00.00-03-00.03-00-00,Folio authority,FOLIO reference to AUTH
FLO_AUTH,00-00-00.00-03-00.03-01-00,Authority value class,Controlled vocabulary class enumerating the values a folio's authority field may take.
FL_NORM,00-00-00.00-03-00.03-01-01,Normative authority value,Authority value indicating the folio carries prescriptive normative content.
FL_DESC,00-00-00.00-03-00.03-01-02,Descriptive authority value,Authority value indicating the folio carries non-normative descriptive content.
FLIO_BND,00-00-00.00-03-00.04-00-00,Folio binding,FOLIO reference to BIND
FLO_BIND,00-00-00.00-03-00.04-01-00,Binding value class,Controlled vocabulary class enumerating the values a folio's binding field may take.
FL_OVRLY,00-00-00.00-03-00.04-01-01,Overlay binding value,Binding value indicating the folio has no parent or child hierarchy and applies as an overlay scoped by selector segments.
FL_STRCT,00-00-00.00-03-00.04-01-02,Structural binding value,Binding value indicating the folio participates in the primary structural tree with a full ancestor chain.
FLIO_PLD,00-00-00.00-03-00.05-00-00,Artifacts listed by manifest,A construct representing the ordered set of artifact references declared within a manifest payload.
FLIO_REL,00-00-00.00-03-00.06-00-00,Folio relations,Relations a folio may hold with other folios such as supersession and reference.
FLO_RLTN,00-00-00.00-03-00.06-01-00,Relation value class,Controlled vocabulary class enumerating the kinds of inter-folio relations a folio may declare.
FL_SUPER,00-00-00.00-03-00.06-01-01,Supersession relation value,Relation value indicating one folio supersedes another within the same overlay lineage.
FL_REFER,00-00-00.00-03-00.06-01-02,Reference relation value,Relation value indicating one folio references another non-superseding folio.
FLIO_HSH,00-00-00.00-03-00.07-00-00,Folio hash,"Hash field set in FLIO_REF carrying SHA-256 digests over manifest, payload, and supersession content."
FLO_HASH,00-00-00.00-03-00.07-01-00,Hash value class,Controlled vocabulary class enumerating the kinds of hashes a FLIO_REF hash field may carry.
FL_HSCOR,00-00-00.00-03-00.07-01-01,Core hash value,Hash value computed over committed FLIO_REF manifest fields excluding hash fields themselves; carried by record_hash.
FL_HSPLD,00-00-00.00-03-00.07-01-02,Payload hash value,Hash value computed over FLIO_PLD entries in order at time of commit; carried by payload_hash.
FL_HSSPR,00-00-00.00-03-00.07-01-03,Supersession hash value,Hash value appended at supersession time chaining from FL_HSCOR and FL_HSPLD plus supersession metadata; carried by supersession_hash.
FLIO_OWN,00-00-00.00-03-00.08-00-00,Folio owner,Field-in-manifest recording the NODE_ID of the folio representing the owner of this folio.
FLIO_CRT,00-00-00.00-03-00.09-00-00,Folio creation date,Field-in-manifest recording the NODE_ID of the date folio for when this folio was committed.
FLIO_SUP,00-00-00.00-03-00.0A-00-00,Folio supersession,Field-pair concept grouping the upstream and downstream supersession directions.
FLO_SPUP,00-00-00.00-03-00.0A-01-00,Supersession upstream,List of NODE_IDs that this folio supersedes; the folios this one replaces.
FLO_SPDN,00-00-00.00-03-00.0A-02-00,Supersession downstream,List of NODE_IDs that supersede this folio; the folios that replace this one.
MODE,00-00-00.00-04-00.00-00-00,Agent modes,A controlled set of categories defining how nodes are expressed and interpreted.
MOD_1,00-00-00.00-04-00.01-00-00,Mode 1,"A mode representing atomic, declarative definitions of objects independent of realization."
MOD_2,00-00-00.00-04-00.02-00-00,Mode 2,"A mode representing governance, rules, and descriptive context for defined objects."
MOD_3,00-00-00.00-04-00.03-00-00,Mode 3,"A mode representing concrete, derived artifacts that implement or realize defined objects."
TYPE,00-00-00.00-05-00.00-00-00,Artifact type classifications,A system defining allowable categories of artifacts within nodes.
TYPE_COR,00-00-00.00-05-00.01-00-00,Files types describing facets of NODE,"An artifact type representing extensible, user-defined classifications beyond the core set."
TYP_MKDN,00-00-00.00-05-00.01-01-00,Markdown node description,Authoritative markdown description of the NODE
T1_DEFNS,00-00-00.00-05-00.01-01-01,Markdown reference section for definitions,Markdown section within a TYP_MKDN artifact reserved for term definitions used by the node.
T1_RULES,00-00-00.00-05-00.01-01-02,Markdown reference section for rules,Markdown section within a TYP_MKDN artifact reserved for the normative rules constraining the node.
T1_CONST,00-00-00.00-05-00.01-01-03,Markdown node constraints,Markdown section within a TYP_MKDN artifact reserved for explicit constraints on the node.
T1_RELAS,00-00-00.00-05-00.01-01-04,Markdown node relations,Markdown section within a TYP_MKDN artifact reserved for the node's relations to other folios.
T1_NOTES,00-00-00.00-05-00.01-01-05,Markdown node notes,Markdown section within a TYP_MKDN artifact reserved for non-normative notes about the node.
TYP_YAML,00-00-00.00-05-00.01-02-00,YAML node definitions,An artifact type representing structured YAML node definitions.
TYP_CSV,00-00-00.00-05-00.01-03-00,CSV,An artifact type representing comma separated text.
TYPE_EXTN,00-00-00.00-05-00.02-00-00,FROID extended type definitions,A category grouping FROID-extended artifact types beyond the core set.
TYP_TXT,00-00-00.00-05-00.02-01-00,Generic text files,An artifact type representing unstructured or general-purpose textual content.
TYP_BLOB,00-00-00.00-05-00.02-02-00,Binary object,An artifact type representing opaque binary data without structured interpretation.
TYP_USER,00-00-00.00-05-00.02-03-00,User defined types,An artifact type representing user-defined classifications beyond the core and extended sets.
TYPE_HED,00-00-00.00-05-00.03-00-00,Artifact file header block,A structured header block encoding node identity fields within an artifact.
NODE_BLK,00-00-00.00-06-00.00-00-00,Node block,The unit of scoping in FROID; an ordered sequence of NODE_SEG resolving to a document via locating segments and to a field via a terminating classifying segment.
BLK_PATN,00-00-00.00-06-00.01-00-00,Block pattern,Structural shape of every NODE_BLK: locating segments terminated by exactly one classifying segment; derived from field-terminality.
BLK_SCPE,00-00-00.00-06-00.02-00-00,Block scoping,"The role a NODE_BLK plays as a boundary for local rules, authority, naming, and supersession."
BLK_COMP,00-00-00.00-06-00.03-00-00,Block composition,The role a NODE_BLK plays as a unit of NODE_ID composition; block count is per-projection; the leading granular is the projection selector.
NODE_SEG,00-00-00.00-06-00.04-00-00,Hexadecimal subunit of NODE_BLK,A two-digit hexadecimal component of a NODE_BLK; the atomic structural primitive of FROID_NS addressing.
SEG_GRAN,00-00-00.00-06-00.04-01-00,Granular segment role,A classification of NODE_SEG within a NODE_BLK as a locating segment that resolves a document within the parent scope of its block.
SEG_BINN,00-00-00.00-06-00.04-02-00,Bin segment role,A classification of NODE_SEG within a NODE_BLK as the terminating classifying segment of its block; classifies a kind of field on the document located by the preceding granular segments.
PROJECT,00-00-00.00-07-00.00-00-00,FROID_NS projection,"Catalog of [FROID_NS] projections. Each child row defines one projection: ordered [NODE_BLK] list, segment-function assignments per block, and [SEG_BINN] controlled vocabularies. RR=N≥1 in any (VV, BB) tree instantiates one child of [PROJECT]."
PROJ_FRD,00-00-00.00-07-00.01-00-00,Framework projection,"Self-defining projection that establishes the [FROID_NS] substrate. Block count and segment roles match the chapters at [NODE_ID] / [FOLIO] / [MODE] / [TYPE] / [NODE_BLK] / [PROJECT]; [PROJ_FRD] is its own self-instantiation."
PROJ_TIM,00-00-00.00-07-00.02-00-00,Time projection,Projection encoding Unix-epoch moments. Block count: 4.
PROJ_PRG,00-00-00.00-07-00.03-00-00,Software programming projection,Projection for software development structure. Block count: 3.
PROJ_PTR,00-00-00.00-07-00.04-00-00,Pattern language projection,"Projection for pattern-language structure; details TBD."
